  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>cubed potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2172.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2172.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2172.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2172.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2172.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, drain your <strong>jumbo king prawns</strong> then add them to the pan and cook for 6-7 min or until cooked through</p><p>Once done, remove the pan from the heat and set aside to cool</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322446876-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322446876-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322446876-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322446876-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322446876-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the prawns are cooking, combine your <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Add a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Stir it all together – this is your<strong> Marie Rose sauce</strong></p>",
